  "cscw_dialogue": [
    {
      "turn_id": 1,
      "role": "Domain_Expert",
      "action_type": "propose",
      "utterance": "我们需要画一个教育系统的流程图，核心是三个模块：课堂服务、LMS门户和学生数据库。我先从Audit节点开始，它代表Education_ClassroomService。",
      "elements_involved": [
        "Audit",
        "Education_ClassroomService"
      ],
      "is_repair": false
    },
    {
      "turn_id": 2,
      "role": "Diagram_Editor",
      "action_type": "clarify",
      "utterance": "明白了，Audit是课堂服务。我看到LMS门户这块需要多个节点吗？Bail、Barg、Code这三个看起来都指向同一个系统？",
      "elements_involved": [
        "Bail",
        "Barg",
        "Code",
        "Education_LMS_Portal"
      ],
      "is_repair": false
    },
    {
      "turn_id": 3,
      "role": "Domain_Expert",
      "action_type": "confirm",
      "utterance": "对，Bail、Barg、Code都是Education_LMS_Portal的不同实例或状态，可以理解为门户的不同功能入口。Define则是Education_StudentDB，学生数据库。",
      "elements_involved": [
        "Define",
        "Education_StudentDB"
      ],
      "is_repair": false
    },
    {
      "turn_id": 4,
      "role": "Diagram_Editor",
      "action_type": "execute",
      "utterance": "好的，我把五个主要节点都建好了：Audit、Bail、Barg、Code、Define。现在来连关系线，Audit应该连到Define？",
      "elements_involved": [
        "Audit",
        "Define"
      ],
      "is_repair": false
    },
    {
      "turn_id": 5,
      "role": "Domain_Expert",
      "action_type": "confirm",
      "utterance": "是的，Audit到Define。另外Code也要连Define，表示代码层面操作数据库。还有Bail和Barg之间是双向的。",
      "elements_involved": [
        "Code",
        "Define",
        "Bail",
        "Barg"
      ],
      "is_repair": false
    },
    {
      "turn_id": 6,
      "role": "Diagram_Editor",
      "action_type": "execute",
      "utterance": "双向关系已加上。Define还要连到Barg对吧？我看Define -- Barg这条线。",
      "elements_involved": [
        "Define",
        "Barg"
      ],
      "is_repair": false
    },
    {
      "turn_id": 7,
      "role": "Domain_Expert",
      "action_type": "propose",
      "utterance": "对，Define连Barg。另外我漏了三个中间节点：Place、Press、Signal、Risk，它们形成一条链。Place指向Press，Signal指向Barg，Risk指向Signal。",
      "elements_involved": [
        "Place",
        "Press",
        "Signal",
        "Risk",
        "Barg"
      ],
      "is_repair": false
    },
    {
      "turn_id": 8,
      "role": "Diagram_Editor",
      "action_type": "clarify",
      "utterance": "Place到Press，Signal到Barg，Risk到Signal。那Risk和Place之间有关系吗？还是它们是独立的起点？",
      "elements_involved": [
        "Risk",
        "Place"
      ],
      "is_repair": false
    },
    {
      "turn_id": 9,
      "role": "Domain_Expert",
      "action_type": "confirm",
      "utterance": "它们是独立的，Risk是风险信号流的起点，Place是另一条分支。Risk→Signal→Barg是一条链路，Place→Press是另一条。",
      "elements_involved": [
        "Risk",
        "Signal",
        "Barg",
        "Place",
        "Press"
      ],
      "is_repair": false
    },
    {
      "turn_id": 10,
      "role": "Diagram_Editor",
      "action_type": "execute",
      "utterance": "都连好了。让我检查一下所有关系：Audit→Define，Code→Define，Define→Barg，Bail↔Barg，Risk→Signal→Barg，Place→Press。完整吗？",
      "elements_involved": [
        "Audit",
        "Define",
        "Code",
        "Barg",
        "Bail",
        "Risk",
        "Signal",
        "Place",
        "Press"
      ],
      "is_repair": false
    },
    {
      "turn_id": 11,
      "role": "Domain_Expert",
      "action_type": "repair",
      "utterance": "等等，Bail到Barg的关系方向我刚才说反了。应该是Bail -- Barg双向，但Barg -- Bail这条我确认一下...不对，双向是对的，但Barg指向Bail的单向也要保留，其实是双向箭头。不过你画的Bail→Barg和Barg→Bail都对。",
      "elements_involved": [
        "Bail",
        "Barg"
      ],
      "is_repair": true
    },
    {
      "turn_id": 12,
      "role": "Diagram_Editor",
      "action_type": "confirm",
      "utterance": "双向关系我理解成两条有向边，Bail→Barg和Barg→Bail。这样符合需求。还有别的要调整吗？",
      "elements_involved": [
        "Bail",
        "Barg"
      ],
      "is_repair": false
    },
    {
      "turn_id": 13,
      "role": "Domain_Expert",
      "action_type": "confirm",
      "utterance": "没有了，这个结构完整了。Audit作为课堂服务入口，通过Define连接学生数据库，同时LMS门户的三个节点Bail、Barg、Code各自有明确的数据流向，Risk和Place作为外部触发源也接进来了。",
      "elements_involved": [
